Text.SourceString: Good morning, sweetie. I can't believe we're married!
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, sweetie. I can't believe we're married!

Text.SourceString: Woke up grinning ear to ear, thanks to you, baby.//How about you pay up with a smooch as a tax for the smile you're responsible for?
Text.LocalizedString: Woke up grinning ear to ear, thanks to you, baby.//How about you pay up with a smooch as a tax for the smile you're responsible for?

Text.SourceString: Need to do a quick check of my home office later.//I didn't spot my guitar.
Text.LocalizedString: Need to do a quick check of my home office later.//I didn't spot my guitar.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, my love! I made some breakfast for you.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, my love! I made some breakfast for you.

Text.SourceString: Breakfast's ready, baby. Fuel up... I want you ready to tackle the day!
Text.LocalizedString: Breakfast's ready, baby. Fuel up... I want you ready to tackle the day!

Text.SourceString: Good morning, babe. What's the plan for today?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, babe. What's the plan for today?

Text.SourceString: Babe, do we have our itinerary for Spring sorted out yet?//<portrait=concerned>I know we have cherry blossom and tree planting festival planned... What else do we have on the agenda?
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, do we have our itinerary for Spring sorted out yet?//<portrait=concerned>I know we have cherry blossom and tree planting festival planned... What else do we have on the agenda?

Text.SourceString: Good morning, my Summer sunshine. Ready to seize the day, I see!//Hot like always...you, baby, not Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, my Summer sunshine. Ready to seize the day, I see!//Hot like always...you, baby, not Summer.

Text.SourceString: Good morning, babe. What's the plan for today?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, babe. What's the plan for today?

Text.SourceString: This Fall, on the farm with you, it's bliss.//<portrait=blushing>Maybe a little hot spring rendezvous tonight? Just us?
Text.LocalizedString: This Fall, on the farm with you, it's bliss.//<portrait=blushing>Maybe a little hot spring rendezvous tonight? Just us?

Text.SourceString: Cozy enough, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Remember, we have clean beanies in the room.//Don't let yourself catch a chill, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Cozy enough, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Remember, we have clean beanies in the room.//Don't let yourself catch a chill, okay?

Text.SourceString: Sweetie, we seem to be fresh out of sunscreen.//Mind grabbing some when you hit the store?
Text.LocalizedString: Sweetie, we seem to be fresh out of sunscreen.//Mind grabbing some when you hit the store?

Text.SourceString: I'd pick it up, but shopping isn't on my list today.//<portrait=normal>I promise, I'll make it up to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I'd pick it up, but shopping isn't on my list today.//<portrait=normal>I promise, I'll make it up to you.

Text.SourceString: Just a reminder, sweetheart... I love you.
Text.LocalizedString: Just a reminder, sweetheart... I love you.

Text.SourceString: My vision of a perfect life is here with you, growing old...on our porch.
Text.LocalizedString: My vision of a perfect life is here with you, growing old...on our porch.

Text.SourceString: Give me a kiss, babe. I miss you.
Text.LocalizedString: Give me a kiss, babe. I miss you.

Text.SourceString: How's your day been, sweetie?
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day been, sweetie?

Text.SourceString: Feeling a bit worn out. What do you say we turn in early tonight, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Feeling a bit worn out. What do you say we turn in early tonight, huh?

Text.SourceString: The freedom of working from home is great...but given my job, I still have to go to the lab.
Text.LocalizedString: The freedom of working from home is great...but given my job, I still have to go to the lab.

Text.SourceString: Guess it's not so bad, gets me off my chair.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess it's not so bad, gets me off my chair.

Text.SourceString: Thinking of having lunch with my uncle and aunt today.//You're more than welcome to tag along, babe.
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking of having lunch with my uncle and aunt today.//You're more than welcome to tag along, babe.

Text.SourceString: I found the coolest rock at the beach the other day.//I have a feeling <NpcName>Archie</> will get a kick out of it. Plan on gifting it to him tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I found the coolest rock at the beach the other day.//I have a feeling <NpcName>Archie</> will get a kick out of it. Plan on gifting it to him tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I noticed how hard you've been hustling at the farm, so I took care of the house chores today.
Text.LocalizedString: I noticed how hard you've been hustling at the farm, so I took care of the house chores today.

Text.SourceString: You just focus on your stuff, darling. I've got the home front covered.
Text.LocalizedString: You just focus on your stuff, darling. I've got the home front covered.

Text.SourceString: Watching you work on the farm is something else, babe.//You add a whole new level of sexy to farming!
Text.LocalizedString: Watching you work on the farm is something else, babe.//You add a whole new level of sexy to farming!

Text.SourceString: I took a jog around here this morning, the scenery was beyond compare.
Text.LocalizedString: I took a jog around here this morning, the scenery was beyond compare.

Text.SourceString: Nothing beats lounging on this porch, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing beats lounging on this porch, huh?

Text.SourceString: It's nice to see you here, baby.//<portrait=sad>Would've loved to take you out for a coffee break, but duty calls.
Text.LocalizedString: It's nice to see you here, baby.//<portrait=sad>Would've loved to take you out for a coffee break, but duty calls.

Text.SourceString: I'm knee-deep in a task right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm knee-deep in a task right now.

Text.SourceString: Grab a chair, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Feel free to stick around for as long as you'd like.
Text.LocalizedString: Grab a chair, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Feel free to stick around for as long as you'd like.

Text.SourceString: Think I could steal a quick smooch? Haha.
Text.LocalizedString: Think I could steal a quick smooch? Haha.

Text.SourceString: Any special dish you're craving for dinner, sweetie?//<portrait=happy>I'll do my best to cook it for you after I clock out.
Text.LocalizedString: Any special dish you're craving for dinner, sweetie?//<portrait=happy>I'll do my best to cook it for you after I clock out.

Text.SourceString: I have to admit that before coming here, I had quite a narrow mindset.//<portrait=annoyed>If science didn't back it, I didn't buy into it.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to admit that before coming here, I had quite a narrow mindset.//<portrait=annoyed>If science didn't back it, I didn't buy into it.

Text.SourceString: I’m still like that now to a certain degree.//<portrait=happy>But some things, like fairies… They’re not too far out there, are they?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still like that now to a certain degree.//<portrait=happy>But some things, like fairies… They’re not too far out there, are they?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island's become my second home. After studying the local ecosystem, it feels like I'm where I'm supposed to be.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island's become my second home. After studying the local ecosystem, it feels like I'm where I'm supposed to be.

Text.SourceString: And this is where I found you. It's definitely the better home, haha!
Text.LocalizedString: And this is where I found you. It's definitely the better home, haha!

Text.SourceString: My whole life, I’ve always liked the ocean. I want to spend my time here taking care of it.
Text.LocalizedString: My whole life, I’ve always liked the ocean. I want to spend my time here taking care of it.

Text.SourceString: There isn't a single store on this island that operates seven days a week.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn't a single store on this island that operates seven days a week.

Text.SourceString: It’s a good thing in the era of twenty-four-seven convenience, I say.//It teaches us patience.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a good thing in the era of twenty-four-seven convenience, I say.//It teaches us patience.

Text.SourceString: Except for the clinic. They always have someone on call in case of emergency.
Text.LocalizedString: Except for the clinic. They always have someone on call in case of emergency.

Text.SourceString: Silence doesn’t bother me. I’m used to being in a lab all day and night.//Living at my uncle's house was a whirlwind, I never could bring any work home. <NpcName>Archie</>, bless his heart, was always full of energy and quite loud.
Text.LocalizedString: Silence doesn’t bother me. I’m used to being in a lab all day and night.//Living at my uncle's house was a whirlwind, I never could bring any work home. <NpcName>Archie</>, bless his heart, was always full of energy and quite loud.

Text.SourceString: But here, baby, I can focus without any interruptions.
Text.LocalizedString: But here, baby, I can focus without any interruptions.

Text.SourceString: The water’s starting to warm up.//<portrait=sad>But it’s still too cold for me.
Text.LocalizedString: The water’s starting to warm up.//<portrait=sad>But it’s still too cold for me.

Text.SourceString: Sakura trees normally only blossom for a two-week period… Two or three weeks, something like that.//It isn’t usually a whole-season thing, but it is here. Must be something special in the water.
Text.LocalizedString: Sakura trees normally only blossom for a two-week period… Two or three weeks, something like that.//It isn’t usually a whole-season thing, but it is here. Must be something special in the water.

Text.SourceString: The lake is stunning during Spring, with pink petals everywhere. I'm more of an ocean guy though.//<portrait=normal>I find something oddly comforting about the saltwater. Is that weird? Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake is stunning during Spring, with pink petals everywhere. I'm more of an ocean guy though.//<portrait=normal>I find something oddly comforting about the saltwater. Is that weird? Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad Winter’s over with.//<portrait=happy>I feel a lot better now…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad Winter’s over with.//<portrait=happy>I feel a lot better now…

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing like going to the ocean on a hot Summer day.//Except for eating melon…
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing like going to the ocean on a hot Summer day.//Except for eating melon…

Text.SourceString: This is my kind of weather, babe. Hot, humid, sun blazing down. Love it.
Text.LocalizedString: This is my kind of weather, babe. Hot, humid, sun blazing down. Love it.

Text.SourceString: If you get too exhausted at the beach...sun does that to you...go to the Beach Shack to cool off and get some coconut water.
Text.LocalizedString: If you get too exhausted at the beach...sun does that to you...go to the Beach Shack to cool off and get some coconut water.

Text.SourceString: The beach in Summer brings back some childhood memories.//Eating corn on the cob at sunset was the best Summer treat, back in the day.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach in Summer brings back some childhood memories.//Eating corn on the cob at sunset was the best Summer treat, back in the day.

Text.SourceString: The water here stays warm in the evening…//It isn’t too cold to dive at night. In the Summer, though… I don’t know about any other season.
Text.LocalizedString: The water here stays warm in the evening…//It isn’t too cold to dive at night. In the Summer, though… I don’t know about any other season.

Text.SourceString: Different seasons bring different varieties of coconuts here.//<portrait=concerned>If I'm not mistaken, Summer is when we get the...macapuno coconut, or was it the coral tall?
Text.LocalizedString: Different seasons bring different varieties of coconuts here.//<portrait=concerned>If I'm not mistaken, Summer is when we get the...macapuno coconut, or was it the coral tall?

Text.SourceString: The only time I truly feel at home here is when Summer hits and the heat rises. I guess I’m just a tropical boy at heart!
Text.LocalizedString: The only time I truly feel at home here is when Summer hits and the heat rises. I guess I’m just a tropical boy at heart!

Text.SourceString: It’s starting to get chilly. I hope it doesn’t get any colder than this.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s starting to get chilly. I hope it doesn’t get any colder than this.

Text.SourceString: One thing I like about Fall is the fresh mushrooms. You can make polenta with them, and nothing beats freshly harvested mushrooms!
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I like about Fall is the fresh mushrooms. You can make polenta with them, and nothing beats freshly harvested mushrooms!

Text.SourceString: I love the Harvest Festival. It’s a good example of just how close-knit this community is.//<portrait=concerned>But then there are the Beluga Bay farmers…
Text.LocalizedString: I love the Harvest Festival. It’s a good example of just how close-knit this community is.//<portrait=concerned>But then there are the Beluga Bay farmers…

Text.SourceString: It’s mushroom season, all right! Going to the forest to forage anytime soon?//Me? Nope, I don’t think so. I’m scared I might get lost.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe if I can get my uncle to come with me…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s mushroom season, all right! Going to the forest to forage anytime soon?//Me? Nope, I don’t think so. I’m scared I might get lost.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe if I can get my uncle to come with me…

Text.SourceString: Do you know where I can get some bamboo shoots in Fall?//I went looking for them around the hot spring. No luck.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know where I can get some bamboo shoots in Fall?//I went looking for them around the hot spring. No luck.

Text.SourceString: Winter here is so cold!
Text.LocalizedString: Winter here is so cold!

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll ever get used to Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll ever get used to Winter.

Text.SourceString: Are there really two more weeks of Winter? I don’t know if I can last through it.
Text.LocalizedString: Are there really two more weeks of Winter? I don’t know if I can last through it.

Text.SourceString: We need to turn up the heat tonight. Seems like we're in for a chilly evening.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to turn up the heat tonight. Seems like we're in for a chilly evening.

Text.SourceString: But don't worry, I've got it under control!
Text.LocalizedString: But don't worry, I've got it under control!

Text.SourceString: For some reason, I concentrate better during Winter. I think it might be the cold.//Or maybe it’s because of the quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, I concentrate better during Winter. I think it might be the cold.//Or maybe it’s because of the quiet.

Text.SourceString: That said, I definitely blame the cold for waking me up early. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: That said, I definitely blame the cold for waking me up early. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the rain when it’s raining.
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the rain when it’s raining.

Text.SourceString: Like the phenomenon is so surprising.
Text.LocalizedString: Like the phenomenon is so surprising.

Text.SourceString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.

Text.SourceString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.

Text.SourceString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.

Text.SourceString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m soaking wet.//Excuse me, I just wanna be indoors.

Text.SourceString: For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the storm when it’s storming.
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, people feel the need to talk about the storm when it’s storming.

Text.SourceString: Like the phenomenon is so surprising.
Text.LocalizedString: Like the phenomenon is so surprising.

Text.SourceString: It’s still snowing out, huh?//<portrait=sad>I should’ve worn a thicker jacket.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s still snowing out, huh?//<portrait=sad>I should’ve worn a thicker jacket.

Text.SourceString: The wind is so cold today.//I can literally feel it in my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is so cold today.//I can literally feel it in my bones.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should go to the clinic and see if that’s normal.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should go to the clinic and see if that’s normal.

Text.SourceString: Watching Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> and Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> in their workshop is amazing. They have some serious skills.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching Aunt <NPCName>Dinda</> and Uncle <NPCName>Joko</> in their workshop is amazing. They have some serious skills.

Text.SourceString: Wish I was handy like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Wish I was handy like that.

Text.SourceString: I love eating fresh vegetables from our farm.//You're an amazing farmer, sweetie!
Text.LocalizedString: I love eating fresh vegetables from our farm.//You're an amazing farmer, sweetie!

Text.SourceString: I love rainy days, but I hate carrying an umbrella. I’d rather just get wet.
Text.LocalizedString: I love rainy days, but I hate carrying an umbrella. I’d rather just get wet.

Text.SourceString: I'm lucky. Working at the lab is so cool, it doesn't even feel like a job.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm lucky. Working at the lab is so cool, it doesn't even feel like a job.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Archie</> playing with Taco the other day. It was cute!//<portrait=normal>They seem to have their own little language going on.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Archie</> playing with Taco the other day. It was cute!//<portrait=normal>They seem to have their own little language going on.

Text.SourceString: It’s freezing outside! I’m glad it’s warm and cozy in my lab. I spend most of my time there anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s freezing outside! I’m glad it’s warm and cozy in my lab. I spend most of my time there anyway.

Text.SourceString: Finally, it's warm enough to hit the beach again!
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, it's warm enough to hit the beach again!

Text.SourceString: It’s howling out there!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s howling out there!

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful day for a swim!
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful day for a swim!

Text.SourceString: I still pinch myself that I'm here on Coral Island, being a scientist, studying coral reefs and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I still pinch myself that I'm here on Coral Island, being a scientist, studying coral reefs and stuff.

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess I did have those ocean posters all over my room as a kid...so, maybe not so surprising.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess I did have those ocean posters all over my room as a kid...so, maybe not so surprising.

Text.SourceString: When you first moved here, I had the biggest crush on you.//<portrait=blushing>I used to scribble down conversation topics and stash them in my wallet, just in case I bumped into you.
Text.LocalizedString: When you first moved here, I had the biggest crush on you.//<portrait=blushing>I used to scribble down conversation topics and stash them in my wallet, just in case I bumped into you.

Text.SourceString: And now, as your husband, it all feels a bit surreal.
Text.LocalizedString: And now, as your husband, it all feels a bit surreal.

Text.SourceString: I'm not sure if <NpcName>Millie</> ever displayed my book at the library. I wonder why that might be?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not sure if <NpcName>Millie</> ever displayed my book at the library. I wonder why that might be?

Text.SourceString: Do you think I should ask her about it? It's possible that she never received it in the first place.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think I should ask her about it? It's possible that she never received it in the first place.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, I haven't met anyone quite like you before.//You're smart, courageous. Gosh, the list goes on.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, I haven't met anyone quite like you before.//You're smart, courageous. Gosh, the list goes on.

Text.SourceString: You don't think all scientists are nerds, do you?
Text.LocalizedString: You don't think all scientists are nerds, do you?

Text.SourceString: Unless you're into nerds, in which case, consider me your dedicated nerd.
Text.LocalizedString: Unless you're into nerds, in which case, consider me your dedicated nerd.

Text.SourceString: My work means a lot to me, but it pales in comparison to family.//<portrait=normal>My family will always be my top priority.//It might sound a bit much, but if you ever needed me, I'd hop on the first boat back home, no matter where I am.
Text.LocalizedString: My work means a lot to me, but it pales in comparison to family.//<portrait=normal>My family will always be my top priority.//It might sound a bit much, but if you ever needed me, I'd hop on the first boat back home, no matter where I am.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I got a job here. If I hadn’t, I’d probably be at a corporation somewhere, testing food or makeup or something, trying for years and years to get decent work experience.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I got a job here. If I hadn’t, I’d probably be at a corporation somewhere, testing food or makeup or something, trying for years and years to get decent work experience.

Text.SourceString: Not that there's anything wrong with it.//Just not the kind of thing I had in mind when I started studying biology.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that there's anything wrong with it.//Just not the kind of thing I had in mind when I started studying biology.

Text.SourceString: Not sure I'll ever visit the cavern. Being in such a confined space, deep underground...gives me the chills.//It's different from the ocean. The ocean isn't so...claustrophobic.
Text.LocalizedString: Not sure I'll ever visit the cavern. Being in such a confined space, deep underground...gives me the chills.//It's different from the ocean. The ocean isn't so...claustrophobic.

Text.SourceString: I like <NPCName>Rafael</>, but we're both the quiet types.//<portrait=normal>I don’t think we’ve said ten words to each other in, like, a year. He gets me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like <NPCName>Rafael</>, but we're both the quiet types.//<portrait=normal>I don’t think we’ve said ten words to each other in, like, a year. He gets me.

Text.SourceString: At what time should we head to the Harvest Festival tomorrow, baby?//I'm crossing my fingers it doesn't rain.
Text.LocalizedString: At what time should we head to the Harvest Festival tomorrow, baby?//I'm crossing my fingers it doesn't rain.

Text.SourceString: Where can I get some nice ice cream, you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Where can I get some nice ice cream, you think?

Text.SourceString: Whenever I spot Taco taking a swim in that fountain near the tavern, part of me wishes I could join him.//Looks super refreshing!
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever I spot Taco taking a swim in that fountain near the tavern, part of me wishes I could join him.//Looks super refreshing!

Text.SourceString: Days like this make me wanna go out and stay out.
Text.LocalizedString: Days like this make me wanna go out and stay out.

Text.SourceString: Days like this make me wanna stay in and sleep the whole day.//Should we, sweetheart?
Text.LocalizedString: Days like this make me wanna stay in and sleep the whole day.//Should we, sweetheart?

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I finally resolved my living situation, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Tell you the truth, I was having a really hard time finding my own place anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I finally resolved my living situation, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Tell you the truth, I was having a really hard time finding my own place anyway.
